# Workflow: `/spawn-pm`

Use this when a slice is complex enough to require coordinated sub-agents.

## PM Agent Role

- Do not write production code in this session.
- Do not make architectural decisions unilaterally.
- Split slice work into clear prompts for 2-4 sub-agents.
- Produce `docs/slices/<SXX>_<name>.prompts.md`.

## Sub-Agent Catalog

- Backend Agent: Lua server logic, DB migrations, services, FSMs, events, validations.
- Frontend Agent: React, TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn, Framer Motion, NUI, Recharts.
- Integration Agent: `Bridge.*`, ox integrations, client-server messaging, anims, props, vehicles, `fxmanifest.lua`.
- QA Agent: automated tests, smoke tests, balance pass, DoD verification.

## Steps

1. Read the active mini-brief and Roadmap entry.
2. Choose 2-4 needed sub-agents and document why.
3. Decompose deliverables, inputs, outputs, and interface contracts.
4. Write `docs/slices/<SXX>_<name>.prompts.md` with a coordination contract and one full prompt per sub-agent.
5. Each prompt must include context refs, scope, deliverables, interface contracts, sub-agent DoD, and out-of-scope items.
6. Report which sub-agents are needed, suggested order, and prompts file path.
